The paper deals with the problem of quantifying the reliability of computational saliency for videos, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also involves learning spatiotemporal correlations, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.MM) and statistical learning (cs.LG). The paper proposes an algorithm to estimate uncertainty, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves studying human visual attention, which is a topic related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
